article_title: Hungary Puts Priority on National Interests
article_text:
The Hungarian prime minister said Saturday he would pursue national interests vigorously rather than follow the model of liberal democracy in his new four-year term in power that began earlier this year.

In a speech delivered near Baile Tusnad, part of neighboring Romania with large numbers of ethnic Hungarians, Viktor Orban pointed to Singapore, China, India, Russia and Turkey as examples of countries that he said were successful on...
